other_tests.changes_over_time: Hip pain decreased to 6/10 after using crutches and reducing weight-bearing activity.

other_tests.findings: Osteopenia of the right proximal femur and acetabulum, no evidence of fracture or avascular necrosis.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Follow-up radiograph revealed normal mineralization of the right femur and acetabulum approximately 13 weeks later.

other_tests.findings: Bone marrow edema of the right femoral head, neck, and intertrochanteric region. Possible early avascular necrosis, likely transient osteoporosis.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Follow-up MRI showed slight residual high-signal intensity in the right femoral head and acetabulum, indicating marked reduction of bone marrow edema.
